Sazka Administrator Says 15 Firms Asked for Information in Sale

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-09-06T15:26:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/sazka-administrator-says-15-firms-asked-for-information-in-sale.html
The administrator for Sazka AS, a
Czech bankrupt lottery provider, received requests from 15 firms
for basic information about the company, Lenka Ticha, a
spokeswoman for administrator Josef Cupka said.  The companies have until Sept. 9 to take part in a sale,
Ticha said in a statement today. The bidders will have until
Sept. 23 to file offers, Ticha said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  